						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 947, Krōdhana, Mārggaśira, [amāvāsyā] • • • sūrya-grahaṇa</hi> corresponding probably to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1025 November 23, Tuesday,</hi> the month being evidently a Pūrṇimānta one. It refers itself to the reign of the Chālukya king <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalladēva</hi> (Jayasiṁha II) and mentions <hi rend="bold">Maduvarmmadēva</hi> who was governing <hi rend="bold">Beṇṇevura twelve</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Manneya</hi> <hi rend="bold">Mallapa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
